headline: Will AI Kill Software? Fear Creeps Beyond 'Saaspocalypse,' Hits IBM, DoorDash
summary: IBM, the 115-year old enterprise tech behemoth, doesn't have a ton in common with 13-year-old food-delivery app operator DoorDash.  IBM stock on Monday was stung with its worst single-day loss since 2000, with a 13% dive prompted by a blog post from AI startup Anthropic.  DoorDash fell more than 6% that same day after a viral Substack post from Citrini Research pegged its business as a potential "poster child" for marketplaces disrupted by AI.

headline: Uber, Lyft stocks surge as Trump scraps Biden-era contractor rule
summary: Investing.com -- Uber Technologies (NYSE:UBER) rose 4% on Thursday, while DoorDash (NASDAQ:DASH) gained 4%, Lyft (NASDAQ:LYFT) climbed 4%, and Maplebear (NASDAQ:CART) advanced 3.3% after the Trump administration moved to repeal a Biden-era rule on independent contractor classification.

headline: DoorDash Refocuses Global Footprint With Market Exits And Hub Closure
summary: DoorDash is exiting Qatar, Singapore, Japan, and Uzbekistan across its Deliveroo and Wolt brands as part of an operational restructuring. The company is also closing Deliveroo's Bengaluru engineering hub and reallocating engineering talent. These changes reflect a focus on international markets where DoorDash reports seeing a clearer path to sustainable scale and long term leadership.
